detaileddescription.para: these static function pointers are needed to register a user handler for the CanModule-C-Wrapper. And no - it is not possible to have a map of pointers, otherwise the threads/mutexes will not work. Why do we have 16 and not 8, since the systec16 has only 8 CAN ports per USB, and no other module has more ? Simple answer: the ISEG HAL can handle up to 16 receiver threads (hardcoded), so let's play is safe. It is a bit unclear what ISEG does with 8..15, but at least CanModule supports this. Most probably the slots 8..15 are unused, though.
